831
01:43:32,570 --> 01:43:33,732
[SPEAKER_51]: Good morning, everyone.

832
01:43:33,752 --> 01:43:34,553
[SPEAKER_51]: Buenos dias.

833
01:43:35,394 --> 01:43:41,323
[SPEAKER_51]: Today, I'm proud to announce that the city of Los Angeles officially recognizes Latino Heritage Month.

834
01:43:41,607 --> 01:44:04,442
[SPEAKER_51]: At a time when our communities are under attack, when ICE raids terrorize our neighborhoods, when a racist federal administration fuels division, and when the Supreme Court has given a green light to racial profiling, we are here to stand tall and proud as Latinos in a moment where we are told to shrink and hide.

835
01:44:04,422 --> 01:44:11,339
[SPEAKER_51]: Today we will honor two extraordinary Latinos whose lives remind us that the fight for justice takes many forms.

836
01:44:12,161 --> 01:44:21,925
[SPEAKER_51]: Carlos Montes, a pioneer and Chicano activist and founding member of the Brown Brace, represents decades of direct action, courage, and organizing in the face of injustice.

837
01:44:22,732 --> 01:44:33,327
[SPEAKER_51]: Francisco Letilier, an internationally recognized muralist, illustrator, and poet has carried forward the tradition of resistance through art, memory, and storytelling.

838
01:44:34,088 --> 01:44:46,967
[SPEAKER_51]: Together, they show us that in the struggle for justice, there is a lane for all of us, whether it's in the streets, through organizing, or by creating art, and that, you know, make sure that our stories are never forgotten.

839
01:44:46,947 --> 01:44:49,171
[SPEAKER_51]: Tomorrow, we continue the celebration.

840
01:44:49,571 --> 01:44:54,058
[SPEAKER_51]: We continue the celebration with El Grito at Grand Park from 5 to 11 p.m.

841
01:44:54,579 --> 01:45:01,029
[SPEAKER_51]: It is our city's largest Latino Heritage Month celebration, a night of culture, music, and community power.

842
01:45:01,690 --> 01:45:06,298
[SPEAKER_51]: In these dark times, we remember that joy is an act of resistance.

843
01:45:06,318 --> 01:45:09,944
[SPEAKER_51]: And as this year's Madrina of the event, I hope to see you all there.

844
01:45:10,364 --> 01:45:13,950
[SPEAKER_51]: I can't wait to see you there, colleagues and everybody from your teams.

845
01:45:13,930 --> 01:45:21,738
[SPEAKER_51]: In just a moment, you'll hear from all the Latino council members, or as I've called us, the Latino caucus, who joined me in this chamber today.

846
01:45:21,798 --> 01:45:23,640
[SPEAKER_51]: We are here and we are proud.

847
01:45:24,041 --> 01:45:25,763
[SPEAKER_51]: We carry a shared struggle.

848
01:45:26,243 --> 01:45:32,650
[SPEAKER_51]: Many of us are children of immigrants raised in households that knew sacrifice, hard work, and resilience.

849
01:45:32,670 --> 01:45:43,161
[SPEAKER_51]: Our presence here is proof of what our parents and grandparents dreamed for us, that despite the obstacles, despite the discrimination, we would claim our place in shaping the future of this city.

850
