02:39:06,320 --> 02:39:18,332
[SPEAKER_44]: In the continued theme of resistance that we've all been discussing today, I wanted to ask all of you to join us today as we honor the memory of Massa Amini.

1471
02:39:19,353 --> 02:39:31,545
[SPEAKER_44]: On September 13, 2022, Massa Amini was arrested in Tehran by Iran's morality police for nothing more than the way she wore her hair.

1472
02:39:32,606 --> 02:39:35,989
[SPEAKER_44]: Three days later, she was dead in a hospital.

1473
02:39:36,965 --> 02:39:45,434
[SPEAKER_44]: Her life was cut short at 22 years old by the physical trauma inflicted on her while in custody of the morality police.

1474
02:39:46,615 --> 02:39:49,898
[SPEAKER_44]: Her story is not a rare occurrence, unfortunately.

1475
02:39:51,200 --> 02:40:01,150
[SPEAKER_44]: For the last two generations, women in Iran have been told how to live, how to dress, and how to behave under the threat of violence and punishment.

1476
02:40:02,243 --> 02:40:08,774
[SPEAKER_44]: This is a system that denies women agency over their bodies, their choices, and their futures.

1477
02:40:10,497 --> 02:40:12,821
[SPEAKER_44]: Masa Amini's death ignited a movement.

1478
02:40:13,623 --> 02:40:17,990
[SPEAKER_44]: Her name has become a battle cry, not only in Iran, but across the globe.

1479
02:40:19,413 --> 02:40:27,627
[SPEAKER_44]: Women, life, freedom, those three words have echoed from the streets of Tehran to the capitals of the world.

1480
02:40:28,315 --> 02:40:38,729
[SPEAKER_44]: Women under oppression have risked everything, removing their head scarves, cutting their hair, standing shoulder to shoulder to demand recognition as human beings.

1481
02:40:38,749 --> 02:40:47,120
[SPEAKER_44]: They stood bravely in the face of brutality, fueled by the truth that no regime is able to silence the voice of women.

1482
02:40:48,161 --> 02:40:51,245
[SPEAKER_44]: The power of courage and resistance shines through the movement.

1483
02:40:51,926 --> 02:40:57,293
[SPEAKER_44]: It reminds us that dignity and equality are forever worth fighting for.

1484
02:40:58,285 --> 02:41:07,822
[SPEAKER_44]: Today, we speak her name to keep her spirit alive, to stand with the women of Iran and with women everywhere who face discrimination and violence.

1485
