1516
02:45:11,512 --> 02:45:22,145
[SPEAKER_43]: Colleagues, it's with heavy heart and a great spirit of sadness that I ask all of us to adjourn in the memory of the Honorable Robert Odell Knight, Sr.

1517
02:45:22,205 --> 02:45:34,941
[SPEAKER_43]: He lived to the age of 89 years old, leaving a remarkable legacy of faith, dedication, and community service.

1518
02:45:36,103 --> 02:45:41,029
[SPEAKER_43]: Mr. Knight was born in SoSo, Mississippi,

1519
02:45:41,009 --> 02:45:45,420
[SPEAKER_43]: In the 1930s, he was four of seven children.

1520
02:45:46,142 --> 02:45:58,393
[SPEAKER_43]: He was raised on a working farm where you learn to work when the sun goes up and keep working until it goes down and your livelihood depends on your labor.

1521
02:45:58,778 --> 02:46:10,875
[SPEAKER_43]: He also was raised in a devout Christian family and church membership was a very important part of his life, later attending Oakwood College in Huntsville, Alabama.

1522
02:46:11,376 --> 02:46:23,233
[SPEAKER_43]: And through his father's guidance, he applied his skills to plastering and construction and completed notable projects across the campus and throughout the city of Huntsville, Alabama.

1523
02:46:23,213 --> 02:46:32,633
[SPEAKER_43]: He served honorably in the United States Army in the late 1950s where he assisted a flight surgeon between Costa Rica, Panama, and Columbia.

1524
02:46:32,731 --> 02:46:48,171
[SPEAKER_43]: His time in Central America and South America broadened his worldview and allowed him to become bilingual in Spanish, a skill that would become very, very important in later years as he moved to the great city of Los Angeles in the 1960s.

1525
02:46:48,832 --> 02:46:56,241
[SPEAKER_43]: He started a family here and began a dual career in elementary education and construction.

1526
02:46:56,221 --> 02:47:04,151
[SPEAKER_43]: While teaching in local schools, he continued to build homes and work with his brothers in the building trade.

1527
02:47:04,852 --> 02:47:11,540
[SPEAKER_43]: And this is before people like Mr. Knight could be in the union and be a part of the big construction companies.

1528
02:47:12,060 --> 02:47:17,487
[SPEAKER_43]: During the 1980s, the construction of the 105 freeway, also known as the Century Freeway,

1529
02:47:17,467 --> 02:47:40,116
[SPEAKER_43]: It prompted the relocation and demolition of numerous homes that were in its path and if you're old enough to remember there along imperial and a hundred between imperial and 120th all those houses that we lost Most in the 15th district, but some in in Athens and other parts of South La Robert saw an opportunity there through

1530
02:47:40,096 --> 02:47:57,801
[SPEAKER_43]: Will point out to this council a community benefits agreement one of the first ones that we ever had In the city of Los Angeles through a community benefits agreement Mr.. Knight was able to require acquire several of those homes at $1 apiece

1531
02:47:58,642 --> 02:48:05,622
[SPEAKER_43]: and had the ingenuity and the drive to figure out how to move them to other places.

1532
02:48:06,224 --> 02:48:13,866
[SPEAKER_43]: So he had houses in West Adams, in South LA, in Inglewood, and other parts of Southern California.

1533
02:48:13,846 --> 02:48:15,629
[SPEAKER_43]: But his involvement didn't stop there.

1534
02:48:15,789 --> 02:48:19,456
[SPEAKER_43]: Once he figured out he could move a house, he figured out he could then build a house.

1535
02:48:19,636 --> 02:48:30,775
[SPEAKER_43]: And so he built houses throughout Southern California, single-family homes, multi-unit apartments, housing developments, and expanded his portfolio

1536
02:48:30,755 --> 02:48:33,038
[SPEAKER_43]: but never became a corporate landlord.

1537
02:48:33,118 --> 02:48:43,411
[SPEAKER_43]: He was the kind of landlord that came personally and knocked on your door if something was broken and stayed there until the plumber or the painter or the fixer got things done.

1538
02:48:44,012 --> 02:48:56,087
[SPEAKER_43]: He believed every person deserved a decent place to live, no matter how wealthy or how poor you were, and he worked to improve the lives of his tenant and was the kind of landlord that we all

1539
02:48:56,067 --> 02:49:11,252
[SPEAKER_43]: long for here in Southern California, not some big giant company across the country that, you know, maybe will take your call or maybe won't, but would show up when something went wrong with the apartments and would keep the apartments at a rate that working people could afford.

1540
02:49:11,593 --> 02:49:17,883
[SPEAKER_43]: He helped stabilize neighborhoods, prevent displacement, and provided affordable options for people throughout the region.

1541
02:49:18,304 --> 02:49:21,349
[SPEAKER_43]: Was an active member in his church,

1542
02:49:21,329 --> 02:49:23,031
[SPEAKER_43]: and built a great family network.

1543
02:49:23,071 --> 02:49:38,107
[SPEAKER_43]: You can see all of the folks standing there on the east side of the gallery who've joined today to celebrate and commemorate the life and the gift of Mr. Knight.

1544
02:49:38,127 --> 02:49:47,657
[SPEAKER_43]: I'm proud to be joined by his wife June and his children, his daughter Giselle and Nicole and his son Lonnie for this

1545
02:49:48,160 --> 02:49:49,061
[SPEAKER_43]: a journey motion.

1546
02:49:49,762 --> 02:49:54,389
[SPEAKER_43]: I would be remiss, and it's a very difficult thing to do.

1547
02:49:54,409 --> 02:49:56,391
[SPEAKER_43]: 89 is a good life.

1548
02:49:57,733 --> 02:50:05,904
[SPEAKER_43]: It's a full tenor of years, but we didn't lose Mr. Knight because of old age or because of sickness.

1549
02:50:05,944 --> 02:50:07,907
[SPEAKER_43]: We lost him because of gun violence.

1550
02:50:09,541 --> 02:50:18,436
[SPEAKER_43]: And so I point that out because the scourge of gun violence visits all of us, unfortunately, what station in life you're in.

1551
02:50:18,496 --> 02:50:25,347
[SPEAKER_43]: You think if I make it to 70 or 60, I'm safe from gun violence in this environment that we have.

1552
02:50:25,608 --> 02:50:29,895
[SPEAKER_43]: And here Mr. Knight was on the doorstep of 90 years old.

1553
02:50:29,875 --> 02:50:40,553
[SPEAKER_43]: And we lose him and mourn him because of the scourge of the gun violence and the availability of guns, the ready availability of guns to frankly people who should not have them.

1554
02:50:41,194 --> 02:50:55,798
[SPEAKER_43]: And so with that, I ask this council and recognize his family and community and ask that the entire city adjourn in the memory of Mr. Robert Knight.

1555
02:50:59,879 --> 02:51:02,183
[SPEAKER_43]: All right, Mr. Nazarian.

1556
02:51:12,120 --> 02:51:13,182
[SPEAKER_44]: Thank you, Council President.

1557
02:51:13,523 --> 02:51:20,655
[SPEAKER_44]: Colleagues, I rise today to honor the memory of Houshmand Arely.

1558
02:51:20,905 --> 02:51:30,462
[SPEAKER_44]: In honoring him, we celebrate a life devoted to beauty, to art, to the sublime, and to the deep, resonant power of music and memory.

1559
02:51:31,304 --> 02:51:42,103
[SPEAKER_44]: Born in 1937 in the historic city of Isfahan in Iran, Houshmand began a journey that would shape the course of Persian music and touch the hearts of the world.

1560
02:51:42,674 --> 02:51:50,965
[SPEAKER_44]: By the age of 13, Houshmand was studying with the great master Taj Esfahani, a revered figure in Iranian classical music.

1561
02:51:51,486 --> 02:52:03,923
[SPEAKER_44]: Through performances at Radio Esfahan and with the Esfahan Students Orchestra, Houshmand's voice became a cherished presence at cultural and academic events throughout the city.

1562
02:52:04,510 --> 02:52:13,282
[SPEAKER_44]: At the inauguration of the Iranian National Television, Houshmand was invited to perform with the prestigious National Orchestra.

1563
02:52:13,763 --> 02:52:20,512
[SPEAKER_44]: His collaborations with the composers and instrumentalists during this time helped shape the soundscape of an era.

1564
02:52:21,173 --> 02:52:31,767
[SPEAKER_44]: His work earned him a UNESCO scholarship, allowing him to travel to the United Kingdom, where he expanded his artistic reach and cultural understanding.

1565
02:52:31,747 --> 02:52:43,625
